title: For Sale:  Antique Remington Leggett Clay Bird Target Thrower
postcontent: Do you want a piece of history?  Here it is!   (2) Antique Remington Legget Auto-Angling Clay Bird Target Throwers.  There are probably just a few people around that have ever shot trap over one of these units and we have 2 for sale as a package. The Remington Model 41 Auto-Angling Trap (an improvement over their earlier Leggett Trap and model 39 Trap) was used during the1943, 1945, 1949, 1951, 1953 and the 1955 Grand Americans. The trap had several improvements to their old Leggett trap plus an auto-angling base was attached. It was developed in 1941 by Remington. The trap was released with a long rod and pipe from behind the trap line prior to the 1951 Grand American. By 1951 the Clyne Brothers of Ohio had developed the Clyne Electric Pullers which were attached to the trap and the targets were released electrically by a button from the scorers table in 1951, 1953 and 1955.  These traps were actually installed and in use at New Milford Rifle and Pistol back in the day.  As a matter of fact the piping is still present in the upper trap house and the lower trap house has the piping and dog house still in place.  These have been in storage for 50 years and are ready for a new home to the serious collector of trap shooting history.  Very heavy cast construction.  They have been moved outside and covered due to some renovations at the club.  Since none of us are old enough to have used these traps we can not be certain that they are complete but examining old pictures it looks like everything is there but are sold as is.  One of the hinge achors is still installed so when a buyer comes forward we will have to get that removed.  We may be able to deliver this as well for a fee.

postcontent: Up for sale is a nice very old military wall tent made out of very heavy waxed canvas. It is hexagon about 14' in diameter, with a 10 1/2' center ceiling. The walls are at minimum 62" high or so. It has provisions for a stove, with canvas flaps to cover the hole if not using. It also has vents up high with covers that can be opened or closed with cordage. All the poles and rope are included. There is webbing with hooks all over the inside to hang mosquito netting, shelves, supplies and the like. This would make a great hunting tent, reenactment prop that is actually functional, or wedding tent (if you wedding has an army-green theme!)This tent is owned by my son's boy scout troop for many years, but it's really too big and heavy to carry for their outings. They mostly go backpacking, and this is most certainly not a backpack tent! You could probably fit a dozen men in the tent, with lot of floor space for cots, cooking apparatus, hunting equipment, etc. I'm sure I could fit 25 boy scouts sleeping on the floor!I'm selling this for my son's troop, with all the proceeds going to his troop's general fund. I can help the buyer take it apart and stow it away. Comes with lots of directions (printed on canvas and sewed into the tent!) and the original matching large canvas bag.Thanks for looking, and have a great day!
